5: These guys don't give up, do they...
9: Alk! There's nowhere left to run...
13:
How incredibly foolish of you. Where
exactly did you expect to flee to?
We're in an enclosed vessel in the
middle of the ocean.
16:
But no matter. More importantly...
Luca... You...
24:
How could the process have failed...
So long as the vessel shared similar
genetic material, it should have
worked... Was I mistaken?
26:
Is it because your genes are
impure? Due to interbreeding with
others?
28:
If that's the case, then you're
absolutely worthless!
37:
Who the hell are you to decide what
he's worth?!
41:
What are you howling on about,
boy? Do you fancy yourself a hero
now?
43:
You're nothing but a single
powerless human. What could you
possibly hope to accomplish?
52:
So that's what the charm was all
about, heh.
54:
There's no one else but us here. No
one else to "observe" us, right?
57: What are you even talking about—
61:
You're probably right. I can't
accomplish much by myself.
64:
But here's the thing...
I'm not alone!
69: Sorry to keep you waiting, Alk!
77: Open before me, gates of the abyss!
85:
The Crimson Blades...
And YOU! What are you—
90:
Alky-Walky! I'm so glad to see you're
all in one piece.
92:
Leave the lady in the lab coat to me!
I'll be back in no time.
101: This is... Captain Zegra, isn't it?
110:
Listen to me. Marina.
And you, my son.
I don't... have long.
113:
What a cruel twist of fate... To think
the great Zegra would fall to a
simple illness.
115:
But at long last, I found it!
The secret to immortality and
eternal life! To surpass man!
117:
This is a power I do not intend to
share with anyone... Save for you.
Only for you, I will make an
exception.
120:
Come to me!
Stand by my side and I will
bequeath upon you my undying
legacy!
125:
I'll stop the recording there. It's not
very pleasant after that—he just
goes on and on about passing
down genes.
127:
He was always talking about that.
That's why I left, you see... He was
completely obsessed with searching
for something to grant him eternal
youth.
129:
He sent countless of our comrades
to their deaths. It was more than I
could bear, so I decided to
leave—but he refused and
challenged me to a battle...
137:
You want me to come to you? When
you don't even know my name?!
And mother... She...
139:
She waited for you!
The whole time—praying you would
come back! But you...
144:
You abandoned her!
Why should I listen to a single word
that you say?!
147:
I believe I told you the last time we
met, Captain. I have no intention of
ever sailing with you again!
151:
No matter what promises of
treasure you try to lure me in with!
